&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Keeper&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Keeper Security is one of the fastest-growing cybersecurity software companies that protects thousands of organizations and millions of people in over 150 countries. Keeper is a pioneer of zero-knowledge and zero-trust security built for any IT environment. Its core offering, KeeperPAM®, is an AI-enabled, cloud-native platform that protects all users, devices and infrastructure from cyber attacks. Recognized for its innovation in the Gartner Magic Quadrant for Privileged Access Management (PAM), Keeper secures passwords and passkeys, infrastructure secrets, remote connections and endpoints with role-based enforcement policies, least privilege and just-in-time access. Learn why Keeper is trusted by leading organizations to defend against modern adversaries at &lt;a href=&quot;http://keepersecurity.com&quot;&gt;KeeperSecurity.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will focus on accessibility testing, conformance and remediation support across Keeper’s React-based product experiences, including the Vault team, Browser Extension team and Admin Console. The ideal candidate has strong knowledge of Section 508 and WCAG standards, hands-on experience with assistive technologies and accessibility testing tools, and the ability to work closely with Product, Design, QA and Engineering to identify issues, document findings and validate fixes. Reporting into the QA organization, this role sits at the intersection of quality assurance rigor and accessibility expertise and will help ensure accessibility is built into the development lifecycle rather than addressed at the end.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct manual and automated accessibility audits across Keeper’s frontend product experiences, including Vault, Browser Extension and Admin Console&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate product experiences against Section 508 and WCAG 2.1/2.2 AA standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test with assistive technologies including screen readers, keyboard-only navigation, screen magnification, voice control and related accessibility tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write clear, reproducible bug reports with severity ratings, accessibility impact, relevant standards references and recommended remediation guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with frontend engineers, designers, product managers and QA teams to help build accessibility into the product development lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate remediations and track accessibility conformance over time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Author and maintain VPATs and Accessibility Conformance Reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help define accessibility acceptance criteria, QA test plans and repeatable accessibility review processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review frontend implementations and UI behavior to identify issues related to semantics, ARIA usage, focus management, color contrast and accessible interaction patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI-enabled tools and workflows where appropriate to improve testing efficiency, issue analysis, documentation and remediation support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
